Three people were shot, including a 16-year-old girl, outside of the Bucks game in Milwaukee on Friday â€” sending panicked crowds on the street sprinting for their lives, video shows. The Milwaukee Police Department confirmed that two men and a teenager were shot near Martin Luther King Drive and Highland Avenue outside of the Fiserv Forum during the final minutes of the Bucks-Celtics playoff game, according to WISN12 News. A 19-year-old man was taken in custody in connection with the incident, according to reports. The wounded men are 26 and 29 years old. Two of the victims were listed in stable condition, The Milwaukee Journal-Sentinel reported. All victims are expected to survive, according to local reports. Video shows scores of fans in the outdoor viewing area known as the Deer District fleeing for cover in the confusion. The Bucks had announced earlier in the evening that as many as 11,000 fans were packed into the area, The Journal-Sentinel reported. Other clips show people screaming as they scatter to safety. First responders soon arrived on the scene to aid the man, who had non-life-threatening injuries, according to reports. A large police presence remained on the scene late Friday night. The Celtics pulled out a win forcing a second-round game seven matchup in Boston on Sunday. 